## RISK ASSESSMENT CRITERIA

### Probability Scale
| Level | Description | Score |
|-------|-------------|-------|
| Very High | Almost certain (90%+) | 5 |
| High | Likely (70-89%) | 4 |
| Medium | Possible (30-69%) | 3 |
| Low | Unlikely (10-29%) | 2 |
| Very Low | Very unlikely (<10%) | 1 |

### Impact Scale
| Level | Description | Score |
|-------|-------------|-------|
| Very High | Severe impact on objectives | 5 |
| High | Major impact on objectives | 4 |
| Medium | Moderate impact on objectives | 3 |
| Low | Minor impact on objectives | 2 |
| Very Low | Minimal impact on objectives | 1 |

### Risk Priority Matrix
- **High (15-25):** Immediate action required
- **Medium (5-14):** Action plan needed
- **Low (1-4):** Monitor and review

## RISK RESPONSE STRATEGIES
- **Avoid:** Eliminate the threat
- **Mitigate:** Reduce probability or impact
- **Transfer:** Shift responsibility to third party
- **Accept:** Acknowledge and monitor
- **Exploit:** Ensure positive risk occurs (opportunities)
- **Enhance:** Increase probability/impact of opportunities

